                                        <![endif]--></div><h2 id=3D"cyber-v=
ulnerabilities-can-lead-to-harm-irl" style=3D"margin-top: 0; font-family: -=
apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; lin=
e-height: 1.11em; font-weight: 700; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; mar=
gin: 1.5em 0 0.5em 0; font-size: 32px; color: #15212A;">Cyber vulnerabiliti=
es can lead to harm IRL</h2><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; line-height: 1=
.6em; color: #15212A;">To me, any knowledge that my data has been unduly ac=
cessed is a violation in its own right. But the Molekule vulnerability coul=
d lead to real-life harm if exploited by the wrong party. Tracking usage da=
ta could help a black hat hacker recognize when a user is or isn=E2=80=99t =
home. Knowledge of filter status combined with an easily identifiable WiFi =
name=E2=80=94such as one Colorado-based dentist=E2=80=99s office that Domin=
ik found in the logs=E2=80=94could be leveraged to launch a hyper-targeted =
phishing scheme.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; line-height: 1.6em; co=
lor: #15212A;">Dominik, who is a professional security analyst, will someti=
mes look under the hood of consumer devices in his free time. After hearing=
 about <a href=3D"https://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/71e214a5?m=3Db503a08a-=
c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f98315f6032b" style=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; color: #1dfd=
c0; text-decoration: underline;" target=3D"_blank">our bounty</a> targeting=
 Molekule=E2=80=99s effort to prevent owners from using third-party filters=
, he borrowed his friends air purifier and got to work. Once he found the i=
ssue, he notified the company, in line with responsible disclosure practice=
s.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; line-height: 1.6em; color: #15212A;"=
>Molekule=E2=80=99s response had some bugs as well. First, Dominik said, th=
ey offered him a $5,000 bounty for his finding. That=E2=80=99s a good thing=
=E2=80=94bug bounties can be an effective way to reward cybersecurity resea=
rchers for identifying problems that could lead to consumer harm so that co=
mpanies can fix them before any damage is done.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 =
1.5em 0; line-height: 1.6em; color: #15212A;">The problem was that the comp=
any asked him to sign an overly-strong NDA that =E2=80=9Cbasically prevent[=
ed] me from ever discussing this vulnerability, even after a fix,=E2=80=9D =
Dominik wrote in a <a href=3D"https://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/a734b4f7?m=
=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f98315f6032b" style=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; =
color: #1dfdc0; text-decoration: underline;" target=3D"_blank"><u>GitHub po=
st</u></a>. This is not how responsible disclosure should work,=E2=80=9D so=
 he declined the bounty.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; line-height: 1=
.6em; color: #15212A;">According to Dominik, after he provided Molekule wit=
h details on how he gained access to user data, the company did not respond=
 to his requests for updates until he posted the vulnerability 90 days afte=
r his initial disclosure. Shortly after that, the company responded and =E2=
=80=9Cmischaracterized the vulnerability as requiring =E2=80=98wrongful reg=
istration=E2=80=99 and claimed it would constitute =E2=80=98criminal trespa=
ss.=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D Mischaracterization or not, the company also acknowle=
dged that it had implemented a patch.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; l=
ine-height: 1.6em; color: #15212A;">=E2=80=9CIt wouldn=E2=80=99t have been =
hard for them to be helpful throughout this process,=E2=80=9D Dominik told =
me. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m not trying to do anything other than make sure the=
ir users are secure. Just be nice.=E2=80=9D</p><h2 id=3D"we-can%E2%80%99t-t=
ake-good-behavior-for-granted" style=3D"margin-top: 0; font-family: -apple-=
system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-heig=
ht: 1.11em; font-weight: 700; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; margin: 1=
.5em 0 0.5em 0; font-size: 32px; color: #15212A;">We can=E2=80=99t take goo=
d behavior for granted</h2><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; line-height: 1.=
6em; color: #15212A;">Being nice=E2=80=94or at least <a href=3D"https://ful=
u-foundation.ghost.io/r/359ff2e8?m=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f98315f6032b" =
style=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; color: #1dfdc0; text-decoration: underlin=
e;" target=3D"_blank">not being evil</a>=E2=80=94is a good place to start. =
But our bounty program has already provided two reasons not to assume that =
IoT manufacturers are going to have our best interests at heart. In additio=
n to Dominik=E2=80=99s cybersecurity concern, <a href=3D"https://fulu-found=
ation.ghost.io/r/00ee6c51?m=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f98315f6032b" style=
=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; color: #1dfdc0; text-decoration: underline;" t=
arget=3D"_blank">Nest bounty</a> winner Cody Kociemba found that first and =
second generation Google Nest devices were <a href=3D"https://fulu-foundati=
on.ghost.io/r/e5cbaphishing@pot?m=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f98315f6032b" style=3D"o=
verflow-wrap: anywhere; color: #1dfdc0; text-decoration: underline;" target=
=3D"_blank">phoning home with troves of user</a> data after thermostat owne=
rs lost access to their smart features.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0;=
 line-height: 1.6em; color: #15212A;">Protecting the cybersecurity research=
 done by Dominik, Cody, and countless other public interest minded hackers =
is another reason that Sec. 1201 of the Digital Millennium Copyright Act ne=
eds reform. Whether on purpose or by accident, there is no guarantee that m=
anufacturers will make sure that our data and our online lives are protecte=
d. Circumventing digital locks will always be necessary to ensure that they=
 are. Researchers shouldn=E2=80=99t have to risk facing a maximum penalty o=
f five years in prison and a $500,000 fine to verify that consumers are pro=
tected.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; line-height: 1.6em; color: #152=
12A;">At the end of the day, ownership is about knowledge as much as it is =
about control. That=E2=80=99s why we=E2=80=99re continuing to push for poli=
cies that protect researchers just as much as they protect the fixers, tink=
erers and owners of the digital devices that have become so central to our =
lives.</p>
